    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#boardman-hayes1973"/>, n. <citedRange>2173</citedRange> (dr.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>003800</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, pp. <citedRange>67, 319</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ὅδε"><unclear>τ</unclear>άνδε</w> 
                    <unclear>τ</unclear><choice><corr>ᾶι</corr><sic><unclear>ι</unclear>α</sic></choice> <persName type="divine" ref="#Kore"><name nymRef="#Κόρα">Κόραι</name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><note>Boardman's reading</note></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Un tel a offert</supplied> cette <supplied reason="subaudible">coupe</supplied> à Korè.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-So dedicated</supplied> this <supplied reason="subaudible">cup</supplied> to Kore.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale ha dedicato</supplied> questa <supplied reason="subaudible">coppa</supplied> a Kore.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Rho has a tailed form, very rare in Cyrenaica (see also <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr110500</ref>). However, being offered to Kore, 
                    the cup was probably inscribed locally.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
